FBIS4-57412 "drlat097_a_94011" FBIS-LAT-94-097 Daily Report 18 May 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Power Plant Generator To Undergo Maintenance Power Plant Generator To Undergo Maintenance FL1805132894 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 18 May 94 FL1805132894 Havana Radio Progreso Network Spanish BFN [Text] Generator unit No. 6 at the Diez de Octubre power plant in Nuevitas is being dismantled for general maintenance. A total of 337 workers will participate in this task, which will take 20 days. Afterwards, they will continue with the repairs to the air-preheating system, change the air ducts, and install a forced-air fan and a seawater pump. The maintenance is scheduled to be done within 70 work shifts, but the workers expect to conclude it in 60, as they did before, with generator unit No. 5. Once the maintenance work is completed, generator unit No. 6 will produce 110 megawatt-hours, in contrast to the mere 45 megawatt-hours currently being produced.
